searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter","doc":"Hosted webhook route registry plus ingress and dispatch bridging.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.ingress_definition/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#t:ingress_definition/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.route_error/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#t:route_error/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.webhook_result/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#t:webhook_result/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.build_definition/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#build_definition/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.fetch_route/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#fetch_route/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.list_routes/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#list_routes/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.register_route/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#register_route/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.remove_route/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#remove_route/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.resolve_route/2","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#resolve_route/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.route_webhook/3","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#route_webhook/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route","doc":"Durable hosted-webhook route metadata.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.callback_topology/0","doc":"Explicit hosted callback topology for a registered route.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#t:callback_topology/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.secret_ref/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#t:secret_ref/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.validator_ref/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#t:validator_ref/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.verification/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#t:verification/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.active?/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#active?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.identity_key/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#identity_key/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.new!/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Route.html#new!/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry","doc":"Package-owned `:telemetry` surface for hosted webhook route resolution.\n\nEvent families:\n\n- `[:jido, :integration, :webhook_router, :route, :resolved]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :webhook_router, :route, :failed]`\n\nMetadata is redacted through `Jido.Integration.V2.Redaction` and remains\nsupplemental to durable ingress and control-plane truth.","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.event_name/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.html#t:event_name/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.emit/3","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.html#emit/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.event/1","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.html#event/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.events/0","doc":"","ref":"Jido.Integration.V2.WebhookRouter.Telemetry.html#events/0"},{"type":"extras","title":"Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"# Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router\n\nHosted webhook route registration and route-resolution bridge above\n`core/ingress`.\n\nOwns:\n\n- route registration, listing, fetch, and removal\n- callback-topology metadata for hosted webhook paths\n- secret-ref resolution through `core/auth`\n- assembly of `Ingress.Definition`\n- package-owned `:telemetry` for route resolution and failures\n- handoff into `core/dispatch_runtime`\n\n`core/ingress` stays focused on normalization and durable trigger admission.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Callback Topology - Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"The router keeps callback topology explicit per route:\n\n- `:dynamic_per_install`\n  - one hosted callback binding per install\n  - resolved directly from `install_id`\n- `:static_per_app`\n  - one app-level callback shape shared across tenants or installs\n  - resolved from `connector_id` plus configured request lookup keys such as\n    `body.account_id`\n\nStatic routes use `tenant_resolution_keys` and `tenant_resolution` to map\nrequest fields onto the right route record.","ref":"readme.html#callback-topology"},{"type":"extras","title":"Route Contract - Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"Registered routes include:\n\n- `connector_id`\n- `tenant_id`\n- optional `connection_id`\n- optional `install_id`\n- `trigger_id`\n- `capability_id`\n- `signal_type`\n- `signal_source`\n- `callback_topology`\n- optional `validator`\n- optional `verification`\n- optional `delivery_id_headers`\n- optional `tenant_resolution_keys`\n- optional `tenant_resolution`\n- optional `dedupe_ttl_seconds`","ref":"readme.html#route-contract"},{"type":"extras","title":"Secret Resolution - Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"Route verification can use:\n\n- a direct `secret`\n- a `secret_ref` carrying a `CredentialRef` plus `secret_key`\n\nWhen a `secret_ref` is present, the router resolves exactly that secret value\nthrough `core/auth` at request time and does not persist the raw secret in the\nroute record.","ref":"readme.html#secret-resolution"},{"type":"extras","title":"Bridge Flow - Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"For hosted webhook requests:\n\n1. resolve the route from install or connector context\n2. resolve the verification secret when needed\n3. assemble `Jido.Integration.V2.Ingress.Definition`\n4. delegate request admission to `core/ingress`\n5. enqueue the admitted trigger into `core/dispatch_runtime`\n\nThe package keeps route persistence local and file-backed so route registration\ncan survive process restarts without pushing that state into `core/ingress`.","ref":"readme.html#bridge-flow"},{"type":"extras","title":"Telemetry - Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"This package owns these stable `:telemetry` families:\n\n- `[:jido, :integration, :webhook_router, :route, :resolved]`\n- `[:jido, :integration, :webhook_router, :route, :failed]`\n\nMetadata is redacted through `Jido.Integration.V2.Redaction` before emission.\nRaw webhook request bodies are intentionally omitted from the emitted metadata.","ref":"readme.html#telemetry"},{"type":"extras","title":"Proof Surface - Jido Integration V2 Webhook Router","doc":"Current proofs:\n\n- `core/webhook_router/test/jido/integration/v2/webhook_router_route_store_test.exs`\n- `core/webhook_router/test/jido/integration/v2/webhook_router_bridge_test.exs`\n- `apps/devops_incident_response`, which proves a hosted signed webhook from\n  route registration through async replay","ref":"readme.html#proof-surface"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}